# Eink News Monitor — environment template
# Copy to `.env` and fill in real values. Never commit `.env` itself (see CLAUDE.md → Architectural Invariant #2).

# --- Supabase (system of record: eink_news_items, eink_daily_reports) ---
# docs/schema.md has the table DDL. Service role key is required because
# writes happen from a trusted cloud routine, not a public client.
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# --- Resend (report delivery — SOP-03 Step 5) ---
# HTTPS API, no SMTP/OAuth — required because cloud routine environments only
# proxy HTTP/HTTPS egress, so raw SMTP can never reach smtp.gmail.com from there.
# Using the unverified onboarding@resend.dev sender, which can only send to the
# email address the Resend account was created with — that address must match
# RECIPIENT_EMAILS below (single recipient only, or verify a domain for more).
RESEND_API_KEY=
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=onboarding@resend.dev

# --- Recipient list (comma-separated; CLAUDE.md → L notes this is config, not hardcoded) ---
RECIPIENT_EMAILS=oliviashih33@gmail.com
